article.description: Marin Maric scored 25 points with 11 rebounds to help DePaul pick up its first Big East Conference win, upending St. John's 91-74 on Saturday.
article.headline: Maric's 25 points help DePaul upend St. John's 91-74
article.linkText: Maric's 25 points help DePaul upend St. John's 91-74
article.story: QUEENS, N.Y. -- Marin Maric scored 25 points with 11 rebounds to help DePaul pick up its first Big East Conference win, upending St. John's 91-74 on Saturday. Max Strus added 22 points and 10 rebounds for the Blue Demons (8-8, 1-3) who had a 46-30 rebounding edge over the Red Storm (10-6, 0-4). Tre'Darius McCallum had 16 points and nine rebounds and Eli Cain chipped in 11 points. A tip shot by Cain midway through the first half gave De Paul a 19-15 lead and they led the rest of the way, building to a 42-38 advantage at the break. St. John's got as close as 51-46 early in the second half but Maric sank a layup and 3-pointer back-to-back after that to help stretch the Blue Demons lead to 58-46 with 14:10 to play and De Paul cruised from there. Bashir Ahmed scored 21 points with seven rebounds for the Red Storm, who have lost four straight.
